cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a design criterion for space-time block codes (STBC) and discusses the code rate, which are topics related to information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses interference channels, which are relevant to networking and communication systems.
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the use of group zero-forcing (ZF) algorithm, which is a technique used in network signal processing.
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a design of STBC for two-user interference channels, which involves computational techniques.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance results of the proposed STBC, which may be relevant to multimedia applications.
